verses.text: And the \nd \+w LORD|strong="H3068"\+w*\nd* spake unto Moses , saying ,

Speak unto the children of Israel , and say unto them, \add Concerning\add* the feasts of the \nd \+w LORD|strong="H3068"\+w*\nd*, which ye shall proclaim \add to be\add* holy convocations , \add even\add* these \add are\add* my feasts.

Six days shall work be done : but the seventh day \add is\add* the sabbath of rest , an holy convocation ; ye shall do no work \add therein:\add* it \add is\add* the sabbath of the \nd \+w LORD|strong="H3068"\+w*\nd* in all your dwellings. \p
¶ These \add are\add* the feasts of the \nd \+w LORD|strong="H3068"\+w*\nd*, \add even\add* holy convocations , which ye shall proclaim in their seasons.
In the fourteenth \add day\add* of the first month at even \add is\add* the \nd \+w LORD’s|strong="H3068"\+w*\nd* passover.
And on the fifteenth day of the same month \add is\add* the feast of unleavened bread unto the \nd \+w LORD|strong="H3068"\+w*\nd*: seven days ye must eat unleavened bread.
In the first day ye shall have an holy convocation : ye shall do no servile work therein.

But ye shall offer an offering made by fire unto the \nd \+w LORD|strong="H3068"\+w*\nd* seven days : in the seventh day \add is\add* an holy convocation : ye shall do no servile work \add therein\add*. \p
¶ And the \nd \+w LORD|strong="H3068"\+w*\nd* spake unto Moses , saying ,

Speak unto the children of Israel , and say unto them, When ye be come into the land which I give unto you, and shall reap the harvest thereof, then ye shall bring a sheaf of the firstfruits of your harvest unto the priest :\f + \fr 23.10 \ft sheaf: or, handful: Heb. omer\f*
And he shall wave the sheaf before the \nd \+w LORD|strong="H3068"\+w*\nd*, to be accepted for you: on the morrow after the sabbath the priest shall wave it.
And ye shall offer that day when ye wave the sheaf an he lamb without blemish of the first year for a burnt offering unto the \nd \+w LORD|strong="H3068"\+w*\nd*.

And the meat offering thereof \add shall be\add* two tenth deals of fine flour mingled with oil , an offering made by fire unto the \nd \+w LORD|strong="H3068"\+w*\nd* \add for\add* a sweet savour : and the drink offering thereof \add shall be\add* of wine , the fourth \add part\add* of an hin.

And ye shall eat neither bread , nor parched corn , nor green ears , until the selfsame day that ye have brought an offering unto your God : \add it shall be\add* a statute for ever throughout your generations in all your dwellings. \p
¶ And ye shall count unto you from the morrow after the sabbath , from the day that ye brought the sheaf of the wave offering ; seven sabbaths shall be complete :
Even unto the morrow after the seventh sabbath shall ye number fifty days ; and ye shall offer a new meat offering unto the \nd \+w LORD|strong="H3068"\+w*\nd*.

Ye shall bring out of your habitations two wave loaves of two tenth deals : they shall be of fine flour ; they shall be baken with leaven ; \add they are\add* the firstfruits unto the \nd \+w LORD|strong="H3068"\+w*\nd*.

And ye shall offer with the bread seven lambs without blemish of the first year , and one young bullock , and two rams : they shall be \add for\add* a burnt offering unto the 
d \+w LORD|strong="H3068"\+w*
d*, with their meat offering , and their drink offerings , \add even\add* an offering made by fire , of sweet savour unto the 
d \+w LORD|strong="H3068"\+w*
d*.
Then ye shall sacrifice one kid of the goats for a sin offering , and two lambs of the first year for a sacrifice of peace offerings.

And the priest shall wave them with the bread of the firstfruits \add for\add* a wave offering before the 
d \+w LORD|strong="H3068"\+w*
d*, with the two lambs : they shall be holy to the 
d \+w LORD|strong="H3068"\+w*
d* for the priest.

And ye shall proclaim on the selfsame day , \add that\add* it may be an holy convocation unto you: ye shall do no servile work \add therein: it shall be\add* a statute for ever in all your dwellings throughout your generations. \p

¶ And when ye reap the harvest of your land , thou shalt not make clean riddance of the corners of thy field when thou reapest , neither shalt thou gather any gleaning of thy harvest : thou shalt leave them unto the poor , and to the stranger : I \add am\add* the \nd \+w LORD|strong="H3068"\+w*\nd* your God. \p
¶ And the \nd \+w LORD|strong="H3068"\+w*\nd* spake unto Moses , saying ,
Speak unto the children of Israel , saying , In the seventh month , in the first \add day\add* of the month , shall ye have a sabbath , a memorial of blowing of trumpets, an holy convocation.
Ye shall do no servile work \add therein:\add* but ye shall offer an offering made by fire unto the \nd \+w LORD|strong="H3068"\+w*\nd*. \p
¶ And the \nd \+w LORD|strong="H3068"\+w*\nd* spake unto Moses , saying ,

Also on the tenth \add day\add* of this seventh month \add there shall be\add* a day of atonement : it shall be an holy convocation unto you; and ye shall afflict your souls , and offer an offering made by fire unto the \nd \+w LORD|strong="H3068"\+w*\nd*.
And ye shall do no work in that same day : for it \add is\add* a day of atonement , to make an atonement for you before the \nd \+w LORD|strong="H3068"\+w*\nd* your God.
For whatsoever soul \add it be\add* that shall not be afflicted in that same day , he shall be cut off from among his people.
And whatsoever soul \add it be\add* that doeth any work in that same day , the same soul will I destroy from among his people.
Ye shall do no manner of work : \add it shall be\add* a statute for ever throughout your generations in all your dwellings.

It \add shall be\add* unto you a sabbath of rest , and ye shall afflict your souls : in the ninth \add day\add* of the month at even , from even unto even , shall ye celebrate your sabbath.\f + \fr 23.32 \ft celebrate: Heb. rest\f* \p
¶ And the \nd \+w LORD|strong="H3068"\+w*\nd* spake unto Moses , saying ,
Speak unto the children of Israel , saying , The fifteenth day of this seventh month \add shall be\add* the feast of tabernacles \add for\add* seven days unto the \nd \+w LORD|strong="H3068"\+w*\nd*.
On the first day \add shall be\add* an holy convocation : ye shall do no servile work \add therein\add*.

Seven days ye shall offer an offering made by fire unto the 
d \+w LORD|strong="H3068"\+w*
d*: on the eighth day shall be an holy convocation unto you; and ye shall offer an offering made by fire unto the 
d \+w LORD|strong="H3068"\+w*
d*: it \add is\add* a solemn assembly ; \add and\add* ye shall do no servile work \add therein\add*.  +  r 23.36  t solemn…: Heb. day of restraint *

These \add are\add* the feasts of the 
d \+w LORD|strong="H3068"\+w*
d*, which ye shall proclaim \add to be\add* holy convocations , to offer an offering made by fire unto the 
d \+w LORD|strong="H3068"\+w*
d*, a burnt offering , and a meat offering , a sacrifice , and drink offerings , every thing upon his day :

Beside the sabbaths of the 
d \+w LORD|strong="H3068"\+w*
d*, and beside your gifts , and beside all your vows , and beside all your freewill offerings , which ye give unto the 
d \+w LORD|strong="H3068"\+w*
d*.

Also in the fifteenth day of the seventh month , when ye have gathered in the fruit of the land , ye shall keep a feast unto the \nd \+w LORD|strong="H3068"\+w*\nd* seven days : on the first day \add shall be\add* a sabbath , and on the eighth day \add shall be\add* a sabbath.

And ye shall take you on the first day the boughs of goodly trees , branches of palm trees, and the boughs of thick trees , and willows of the brook ; and ye shall rejoice before the \nd \+w LORD|strong="H3068"\+w*\nd* your God seven days.\f + \fr 23.40 \ft boughs of goodly trees: Heb. fruit of, etc\f*

And ye shall keep it a feast unto the \nd \+w LORD|strong="H3068"\+w*\nd* seven days in the year. \add It shall be\add* a statute for ever in your generations : ye shall celebrate it in the seventh month.
Ye shall dwell in booths seven days ; all that are Israelites born shall dwell in booths :
That your generations may know that I made the children of Israel to dwell in booths , when I brought them out of the land of Egypt : I \add am\add* the \nd \+w LORD|strong="H3068"\+w*\nd* your God.
And Moses declared unto the children of Israel the feasts of the \nd \+w LORD|strong="H3068"\+w*\nd*.
